ormation and implementation, and criminal justice to show how the innovative legal strategies employed by anti-rape advocates actually undermined some of their central claims. But even as its more radical elements were thwarted, pieces of the rape law reform project were seized upon by conservative policy-makers and used to justify new initiatives that often prioritize the interests and rights of criminal justice actors or medical providers over the needs of victims.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAnti-rape movementxUnited States. 0aAnti-rape movementzUnited States. 0aFeminist theoryxUnited States. 0aFeminist theoryzUnited States. 0aLaw reformxUnited States. 0aLaw reformzUnited States. 0aRape victimsxLegal status, laws, etcxUnited States. 0aRape victimsxLegal status, laws, etczUnited States. 0aRape victimsxLegal status, laws, etc.zUnited States. 0aRapexUnited States. 0aRapezUnited States. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081470793740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814725214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814725214/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK